Question: One image contains only whole, unpeeled lemons, while the other image contains one lemon cut in half, and at least as many unpeeled lemons as the image with only unpeeled lemons.

Reference Answer: False

Left image URL: https://i.pinimg.com/originals/54/ce/9e/54ce9eddb75d8e5af19d8ce7231f2391.jpg

Right image URL: http://www.realfoodforlife.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/lemon-close-up-3.jpg

Original program:

```
ANSWER0=VQA(image=LEFT,question='How many unpeeled lemons are in the image?')
ANSWER1=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='How many unpeeled lemons are in the image?')
ANSWER2=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Are there any cut lemons in the image?')
ANSWER3=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Are there any cut lemons in the image?')
ANSWER4=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER0} == 0 and {ANSWER2}')
ANSWER5=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER1} > 0 and {ANSWER3}')
ANSWER6=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER1} >= {ANSWER0}')
ANSWER7=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER4} xor {ANSWER5} and {ANSWER6}')
FINAL_ANSWER=RESULT(var=ANSWER7)
```
